{"type":"message","id":"2c3ac0fd","parentId":"318e0fc6","timestamp":"2026-04-07T06:48:18.576Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Team Configuration**\n\nI'm currently focused on configuring the `~/.openclaw/workspace/` files to establish a multi-agent software development team with persistent memory. I'm exploring the project context to understand the required configuration points for long-term knowledge retention and collaborative workflows. The goal is a robust setup.\n\n\n**Defining Agent Roles**\n\nI've examined the key configuration files, specifically `AGENTS.md`, to determine role assignments within the team setup. The \"Producer\" role, orchestrated by the main agent (Lobster), appears crucial for spawning subagents and managing workflows. I'm exploring the implications of this producer-subagent dynamic for a software development company context, with a focus on long-term memory integration for each role.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2a00aaab1bc17b24","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -R /Users/hh/Downloads/Claude-Code-Game-Studios-main/.claude/agents/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gemini-3-flash","usage":{"input":13898,"output":39,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":13937,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775544489420,"responseId":"chatcmpl-954e29ba-078d-4a6d-afa5-fe809a8ddb62"}}
